":"Bretagne, Frankrijk"},"en":{"about 1106–1146":"about 1106–1146","1106–1146":"1106–1146","1110–Female":"1110–Deceased","1145–1248":"1145–1248","–Male":"Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","before 1106":"before 1106","1106":"1106","1248":"1248","liv 1110":"1110","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1106":"about 1106","1110":"1110","Europe":"Europe","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland","Penthierre, Brittany, France":"Brittany, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Crawford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and English: habitational name from any of various places called Crawford, primarily the one in Lanarkshire (Scotland), and possibly also from the one in Lancashire. Both are named in Old English with <i>crāwe</i> ‘crow’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[{"name":"Crafford","meanings":["English (Cumberland) and Scottish: variant of   Crawford  ."]},{"name":"Crofoot","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Crawford  .","English: variant of<b>Crowfoot</b>, a nickname for someone with splayed feet or someother deformity of the foot, from Old English <i>crāwe</i> ‘crow’ +<i>fōt</i> ‘foot’. In Middle English <i>crou-fot</i> also denotedthe buttercup, and it may be from this sense that the name arose,although the reason for its adoption is unclear."]},{"name":"Crofut","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant of   Crawford   or <b>Crowfoot</b> (see   Crofoot  )."]}]},{"name":"Reginald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Norman origin, derived from <i>Reginaldus</i>, a Latinized form of   Reynold   influenced by Latin <i>regina</i> ‘queen’. The full form is now regarded as very formal, and bearers generally shorten it to   Reg   in ordinary usage."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Reginald Crawford was born about 1106, in Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland as the son of Galfridus Crawford and Eve Swane. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Sweinsdotter. He died in 1146, in Scotland, at the age of 41."},"et":{"about 1106–1146":"umbes 1106–1146","1106–1146":"1106–1146","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","1145–1248":"1145–1248","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","before 1106":"enne 1106","1106":"1106","1248":"1248","liv 1110":"1110","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1106":"umbes 1106","1110":"1110","Europe":"Europe","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland","Penthierre, Brittany, France":"Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1106–1146":"noin 1106–1146","1106–1146":"1106–1146","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","1145–1248":"1145–1248","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1106":"ennen vuotta 1106","1106":"1106","1248":"1248","liv 1110":"1110","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1106":"noin 1106","1110":"1110","Europe":"Europe","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland","Penthierre, Brittany, France":"Bretagne, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1106–1146":"environ 1106–1146","1106–1146":"1106–1146","1110–Female":"1110–Décédée","1145–1248":"1145–1248","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","before 1106":"avant 1106","1106":"1106","1248":"1248","liv 1110":"1110","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1106":"environ 1106","1110":"1110","Europe":"Europe","Crawford, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Crawford, Lanarkshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Loudon, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Loudon, Ayrshire, Écosse","Penthierre, Brittany, France":"Bretagne, France","lifeSummary":"Reginald Crawford est né environ 1106, à Loudon, Ayrshire, Écosse, fils de Galfridus Crawford et Eve Swane. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Margaret Sweinsdotter. Il est décédé en 1146, à Écosse, à l’âge de 41 ans."},"de":{"about 1106–1146":"um 1106–